<abstract><t>SMTP Mail Transfer Agent Strict Transport Security (SMTP STS) is a mechanism enabling mail service providers to declare their ability to receive TLS-secured connections and an expected validity of certificates presented by their MX hosts, and to specify whether sending SMTP servers should refuse to deliver to MX hosts that do not offer TLS with a trusted server certificate.</t></abstract>

